data.text:
3BBR-FM broadcasts a variety of music, local news and interviews to Baw Baw Shire in the West Gippsland region of Victoria, Australia on 103.1 FM and streaming online. West Gippsland Community Radio Inc. is a not-for-profit organisation run entirely by volunteers to serve its local community. We offer opportunities for people to learn radio production and public speaking skills in a supportive environment.

Yarragon Studio Festival – Winter Feast Highlights

3BBR recently spent an entire afternoon immersed in three concerts featuring the wind quintet Reeds Bending , mezzo-soprano Dimity Shepherd and the multi-faceted actor Richard Piper, punctuated by excellent local food and wine. Join us in the 3BBR FM Concert Hall… » read more

Joshua Hooke in Concert

The remarkably versatile and exciting young pianist Joshua Hooke recently gave a recital at Yarragon Studio, and 3BBR was there to record it. Listen back to the broadcast in the 3BBR FM Concert Hall on Sunday 28th July 2024. Originally… » read more

“Gippsland Live” features the 2024 Boolarra Folk Festival

3BBR-FM was there for the 21st Anniversary of the multi-award winning Boolarra Folk Festival, recording every concert for Gippsland Live, our weekly showcase of local live performances. Again, thousands of people flocked to Boolarra in early March for the festival,… » read more
